Tim Sackton: You actually… the other thing you see is that as the mist is sort of rolling down, and it's curling around the bottom of something, and you see…

1759
02:29:20.400 --> 02:29:26.570
Tim Sackton: Like, along the bottom, the bottom row of Hobgoblin's feet are not standing on the ground.

1760
02:29:26.840 --> 02:29:32.700
Tim Sackton: there's, like, a thousand… Little, like, metallic…

1761
02:29:33.690 --> 02:29:36.859
Tim Sackton: feet, that are, like, appearing and disappearing, and…

1762
02:29:37.110 --> 02:29:40.199
Tim Sackton: slowly pulling… So it's a meca sentiment.

1763
02:29:40.200 --> 02:29:40.800
Mike: Pete?

1764
02:29:43.960 --> 02:29:49.720
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Does the… just out of curiosity, is the size… if this is one thing that…

1765
02:29:49.890 --> 02:30:03.400
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): thousands are riding on. Does the size of that thing match the size of the thing that shot its pseudopod, or tentacle, or whatever? Like, could that conceivably be the same thing that we ran into in Innocent Gay?

1766
02:30:04.200 --> 02:30:08.820
Tim Sackton: Mmm… ….

1767
02:30:10.220 --> 02:30:14.999
Mike: But the shape is very different. That was a blob, this is like a line.

1768
02:30:16.170 --> 02:30:19.940
Mike: Did Kenzo sense any… living thing?

1769
02:30:20.640 --> 02:30:23.999
Mike: With a soul? No. You didn't sense anything with SoulSight, right?

1770
02:30:26.110 --> 02:30:30.020
Mike: This breach is either a con- this thing's either a construct, or, like…

1771
02:30:30.250 --> 02:30:31.860
Mike: It can't have a soul, right?

1772
02:30:32.870 --> 02:30:36.469
Mike: Can it even have a consciousness? I mean, or it could be hidden soul set, I guess.

1773
02:30:39.820 --> 02:30:41.059
Mike: I think it's a mech.

1774
02:30:43.700 --> 02:30:44.149
David S. Kong: a mech.

1775
02:30:45.090 --> 02:30:48.430
Mike: Well, it doesn't… you didn't sense this creature, right?

1776
02:30:48.560 --> 02:30:53.449
Mike: Don't you think it's, like, a mechanical construct? Not a… does it look?

1777
02:30:53.720 --> 02:30:54.809
Mike: Made of metal?

1778
02:30:55.190 --> 02:30:57.939
Tim Sackton: I mean, you can't tell, it's all covered in ash.

1779
02:30:58.100 --> 02:31:00.900
Tim Sackton: You gotta fly into the ash if you want to learn more.

1780
02:31:00.900 --> 02:31:03.970
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): The bat is flying in to its doom.

1781
02:31:05.630 --> 02:31:11.950
Tim Sackton: So the bat flies up and dips down to the top, into the top of the ash, and you can see, like.

1782
02:31:13.070 --> 02:31:14.500
Tim Sackton: As soon as you dip…

1783
02:31:14.630 --> 02:31:19.899
Tim Sackton: Down below the sort of billowing clouds of ash, there's actually a bit of a clear space.

1784
02:31:20.460 --> 02:31:25.630
Tim Sackton: And you see… What must be a line of…

1785
02:31:26.540 --> 02:31:31.069
Tim Sackton: You know, 600 hobgoblins or so from end to end.

1786
02:31:31.270 --> 02:31:34.210
Tim Sackton: Stack 3 on each side.

1787
02:31:34.320 --> 02:31:36.510
Tim Sackton: So… you know.

1788
02:31:37.470 --> 02:31:48.150
Tim Sackton: 1,800 hobgoblins clinging to the sides of this thing, which is a… 400 foot long… centipede made out of…

1789
02:31:49.530 --> 02:31:52.089
Tim Sackton: It doesn't actually look like metal, it's like…

1790
02:31:52.220 --> 02:31:59.049
Tim Sackton: It's, like, shifting and shimmering as it moves, it's like… it's almost like it's…

1791
02:31:59.720 --> 02:32:05.260
Tim Sackton: it's materializing one step forward every time it moves. It doesn't look like there's anything

1792
02:32:05.460 --> 02:32:10.780
Tim Sackton: There's no, like, joints actually moving, except at the top, these big, open, gaping…

1793
02:32:11.860 --> 02:32:20.900
Tim Sackton: wounds that are, like, flaps of metallic skin, almost, going like this. And as they move, ash billows out from the inside.

1794
02:32:21.090 --> 02:32:22.469
Tim Sackton: Of this creature.

1795
02:32:23.620 --> 02:32:29.199
Tim Sackton: And between each billow, you get this… Brief, clear vision.

1796
02:32:29.620 --> 02:32:36.310
Tim Sackton: And you can see, like, a few hundred feet ahead, … standing…

1797
02:32:36.730 --> 02:32:40.790
Tim Sackton: platform on the head, I guess, of this thing.

1798
02:32:41.140 --> 02:32:43.679
Tim Sackton: is a Hobgoblin.

1799
02:32:44.020 --> 02:32:47.770
Tim Sackton: wearing, … What seems like a…

1800
02:32:48.580 --> 02:32:53.300
Tim Sackton: Metal suit of a similar material that just clings to their skin.

1801
02:32:53.820 --> 02:32:59.860
Tim Sackton: Almost forming an entire, just, like, metallic sheen around their body, and they're holding up

1802
02:33:00.690 --> 02:33:03.569
Tim Sackton: A spear in this… in their hand.

1803
02:33:04.540 --> 02:33:10.569
Tim Sackton: And looking forward, and it… and as you glance at this, one of the Hobgoblins…

1804
02:33:10.730 --> 02:33:15.350
Tim Sackton: riding near U-turns and looks, and then quickly…

1805
02:33:15.520 --> 02:33:21.310
Tim Sackton: Reaches out with their hand, grabs the bat, Brings out a knife.

1806
02:33:21.910 --> 02:33:23.509
Tim Sackton: slices its head.

1807
02:33:24.460 --> 02:33:25.629
Tim Sackton: And then eats it.

1808
02:33:33.120 --> 02:33:36.480
David S. Kong: Tim, can I sense that… Leader, dude?

1809
02:33:37.710 --> 02:33:41.820
Tim Sackton: A hobgoblin, presumably, because you don't sense anything that's not a hobgoblin.

1810
02:33:45.580 --> 02:33:48.370
David S. Kong: These are all, like, real Hobgoblins, they're not, like, you know….

1811
02:33:49.660 --> 02:33:50.270
Tim Sackton: Yeah.

1812
02:33:53.200 --> 02:33:54.879
David S. Kong: I mean, they're writing a….

1813
02:33:55.490 --> 02:33:58.439
Tim Sackton: giant mecha centipede, but they're real hot dogs.

1814
02:33:58.440 --> 02:34:00.199
David S. Kong: Yeah, yeah. …

1815
02:34:00.610 --> 02:34:08.129
David S. Kong: Guys, I slept for a little… I fell asleep over there. What's going on? Where are we… why is there a giant centimede with Hoglobins?

1816
02:34:08.650 --> 02:34:09.939
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): I don't know the why.

1817
02:34:10.600 --> 02:34:12.090
Mike: the Hobgoblins…

1818
02:34:13.270 --> 02:34:17.960
Mike: are coming… I mean, we got the part… did you get the part where the Hobgoblins are coming to kill…

1819
02:34:18.910 --> 02:34:21.709
Mike: this refounded alliance of Orbez.

1820
02:34:22.340 --> 02:34:23.440
David S. Kong: What's Orbaz again?

1821
02:34:23.440 --> 02:34:35.879
Mike: That's this plateau that… where Marcella's been living, that apparently the Cult of Beryl is one of their leaders, or something like that? We don't know that much about it, we just… Marcella asked us for help, we showed up.

1822
02:34:36.110 --> 02:34:44.269
Mike: And then, she said, like, the hobgobs will be here in a week. And we said, let's turn into eagles and fly out and scout them. And now we're scouting them.

1823
02:34:44.520 --> 02:34:47.410
David S. Kong: Got it, okay, and this is what we're seeing. Okay. Alright.

1824
02:34:48.580 --> 02:34:52.330
David S. Kong: I mean, I could get even closer, I could turn it into an astral being.

1825
02:34:55.270 --> 02:34:57.559
Tim Sackton: It doesn't make you immune to damage.

1826
02:34:58.630 --> 02:35:02.030
David S. Kong: But it makes me… what?

1827
02:35:02.590 --> 02:35:07.130
David S. Kong: Well, now that I'm level, there's a… there's a whole thing… can't I… can't I turn myself invisible now?

1828
02:35:08.270 --> 02:35:10.009
Mike: You are currently invisible.

1829
02:35:10.210 --> 02:35:10.640
David S. Kong: None of that.

1830
02:35:10.640 --> 02:35:12.080
Tim Sackton: You are currently invisible.

1831
02:35:12.080 --> 02:35:16.160
David S. Kong: No, no, no, no, but I remember reading something like, … 18th floor.

1832
02:35:16.160 --> 02:35:20.430
Tim Sackton: … No, you got… ….

1833
02:35:20.430 --> 02:35:22.459
David S. Kong: What's the thing I got for 18th level, Tim?

1834
02:35:24.030 --> 02:35:25.700
Tim Sackton: at 18th level.

1835
02:35:29.320 --> 02:35:32.019
Tim Sackton: … you got….

1836
02:35:33.650 --> 02:35:34.149
David S. Kong: I thought I'm.

1837
02:35:34.150 --> 02:35:41.230
Tim Sackton: At the start of your turn, you can spend 3 focus points to have resistance to all damage except force for the next minute.

1838
02:35:44.220 --> 02:35:45.459
David S. Kong: Where, where is that?

1839
02:35:46.090 --> 02:35:47.899
Tim Sackton: Superior Defense.

1840
02:35:48.350 --> 02:35:48.830
David S. Kong: Huh?

1841
02:35:48.830 --> 02:35:49.620
Mike: Pretty good.

1842
02:35:54.610 --> 02:36:00.049
David S. Kong: I could've sworn I, I saw something where I actually, I actually, I actually turned full-on invisible.

1843
02:36:01.360 --> 02:36:05.059
Tim Sackton: Oh, I think that's the old monk, the unrevised monk.

1844
02:36:06.010 --> 02:36:07.150
David S. Kong: Aw, man…

1845
02:36:07.250 --> 02:36:12.459
David S. Kong: Because I remember seeing that the last time, and I was like, oh, shit, I'm in, like, fucking Invincible. Because, like, it was literally.

1846
02:36:12.460 --> 02:36:13.300
Tim Sackton: Wow.

1847
02:36:13.940 --> 02:36:20.820
Tim Sackton: That was not actually that useful, because it took an action, and it only lasts for a minute, which means you basically waste your first turn in combat.

1848
02:36:22.140 --> 02:36:27.560
Tim Sackton: This is much better because it doesn't take an action, you just get resistance if you spend 3 focus points.

1849
02:36:29.050 --> 02:36:30.420
David S. Kong: Yeah, okay, fine.

1850
02:36:31.350 --> 02:36:34.310
David S. Kong: Well, it would have been cool to do this to….

1851
02:36:34.980 --> 02:36:37.399
Tim Sackton: Be in… be invisible.

1852
02:36:41.120 --> 02:36:41.950
David S. Kong: Hmm….

1853
02:36:43.840 --> 02:36:47.689
Tim Sackton: Resistance to all damage except force effectively doubles your hit points, though.

1854
02:36:48.830 --> 02:36:50.160
David S. Kong: Yeah, that's pretty cool.

1855
02:36:52.730 --> 02:36:53.920
David S. Kong: That's what you guys wanna do?

1856
02:36:55.690 --> 02:36:58.419
Mike: So how close… we're, like, a couple hundred feet away.

1857
02:36:59.280 --> 02:37:01.920
Tim Sackton: No, you're, like, half a mile away.

1858
02:37:02.120 --> 02:37:02.790
Mike: Okay.

1859
02:37:02.820 --> 02:37:09.130
Tim Sackton: Only the bat was a couple hundred feet away and is now dead after being eaten by a hobgoblin.

1860
02:37:09.770 --> 02:37:16.069
David S. Kong: Can we, like, read their minds? Or, … you know, we just need to learn a little bit more about what the fuck is going on here, we don't know the plot at all, right?

1861
02:37:18.520 --> 02:37:21.540
Mike: Yeah, I could read their… I mean, I can do lots of things if I'm within 30 feet.

1862
02:37:22.020 --> 02:37:28.120
David S. Kong: Yeah, why don't you, why don't you get within 30 feet, and then, do some, like, mind reading, some, like, you know…

1863
02:37:28.740 --> 02:37:30.240
David S. Kong: Like, what the fuck's going on here?

1864
02:37:31.870 --> 02:37:34.330
Tim Sackton: Well, you're gonna turn visible.

1865
02:37:37.430 --> 02:37:38.240
Mike: the…

1866
02:37:42.150 --> 02:37:46.389
Mike: Does… you lose invisibility? Hold on, does a magic action… hold on….

1867
02:37:47.180 --> 02:37:48.769
Tim Sackton: Just cast a spell.

1868
02:37:50.190 --> 02:37:50.820
Mike: Now.

1869
02:37:51.250 --> 02:38:01.550
Mike: So… Seeker could turn… Me into a… Ant.

1870
02:38:07.440 --> 02:38:08.990
Tim Sackton: And still be invisible.

1871
02:38:09.170 --> 02:38:11.350
Mike: And that wouldn't make Sickert turn visible.

1872
02:38:12.690 --> 02:38:13.490
Tim Sackton: Correct.

1873
02:38:18.360 --> 02:38:21.230
Mike: But any spells I cast stay cast.

1874
02:38:23.020 --> 02:38:26.709
Mike: The problem is that Detect Thoughts only has a 1 minute duration.

1875
02:38:29.200 --> 02:38:34.580
Tim Sackton: An ant's gonna struggle to cross any reasonable distance in one minute.

1876
02:38:36.900 --> 02:38:42.029
Mike: Wow, I need to be… Right, it's tough to get within 30 feet of this guy.

1877
02:38:45.430 --> 02:38:47.029
Mike: 30 feet's really short.

1878
02:38:48.470 --> 02:38:51.569
Tim Sackton: I mean, 30 feet is standing inside the ash cloud.

1879
02:38:53.300 --> 02:38:55.820
Tim Sackton: Like, it's billowing enough that…

1880
02:38:56.210 --> 02:39:00.170
Tim Sackton: If you want to be within 30 feet of a hobgoblin, you've got to be basically in…

1881
02:39:00.780 --> 02:39:03.600
Tim Sackton: At the edge, or just inside the ash pod.

1882
02:39:05.960 --> 02:39:08.369
Mike: Are there any, like, stragglers?

1883
02:39:09.600 --> 02:39:13.050
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Yeah, what's the backend of this thing look like?

1884
02:39:14.150 --> 02:39:17.439
Tim Sackton: Nobody is walking, everybody is riding.

1885
02:39:22.500 --> 02:39:26.540
David S. Kong: Tim, the mechanical centipede thing? No soul.

1886
02:39:27.260 --> 02:39:28.140
Tim Sackton: No soul.

1887
02:39:29.090 --> 02:39:30.319
David S. Kong: Is it… is it magical?

1888
02:39:30.420 --> 02:39:32.520
David S. Kong: Is it like a construct? What is it?

1889
02:39:33.550 --> 02:39:37.100
Tim Sackton: I mean, yes, obviously it's magical, I mean…

1890
02:39:40.400 --> 02:39:44.370
Tim Sackton: What it is, though, is very hard to say. I mean, you've never seen anything like this before.

1891
02:39:45.510 --> 02:39:46.090
David S. Kong: Hmm.

1892
02:39:51.190 --> 02:40:00.869
Mike: … It seems quite difficult to use any magic to investigate these guys.

1893
02:40:01.380 --> 02:40:02.320
Mike: Wow, our magic.

1894
02:40:02.320 --> 02:40:03.370
David S. Kong: What if we kidnapped.

1895
02:40:03.370 --> 02:40:10.620
Mike: Well, that's what I was wondering, is like, could we kidnap one of them, or kill one of them? I can't speak with Dead if we just kill one of them?

1896
02:40:10.620 --> 02:40:11.570
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): be handy.

1897
02:40:12.820 --> 02:40:14.159
David S. Kong: Yeah, let's kill one.

1898
02:40:16.440 --> 02:40:17.840
David S. Kong: Let's go on and take a prisoner.

1899
02:40:19.000 --> 02:40:20.680
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): How? How?

1900
02:40:21.320 --> 02:40:24.770
Tim Sackton: Yeah, I mean, that's a noble goal.

1901
02:40:25.040 --> 02:40:27.449
Tim Sackton: But what are your characters actually doing?

1902
02:40:32.140 --> 02:40:39.249
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Could we… can we animal shape to be giant eagles and swoop down and pick one up and fly away with it?

1903
02:40:41.930 --> 02:40:44.699
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Is that a… is that a thing? Is that an option?

1904
02:40:49.600 --> 02:40:50.480
David S. Kong: Or…

1905
02:40:50.630 --> 02:41:04.889
David S. Kong: let's keep that on the table, or we stealthily, well be stealthily, pick someone off from behind. Like, we, like, knock off one of the ones on the very, very end, you know? Create a little… create a little, you know, just… just fuckin'… sneak attack.

1906
02:41:06.170 --> 02:41:06.780
David S. Kong: Knock one.

1907
02:41:06.780 --> 02:41:07.510
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Yes.

1908
02:41:08.370 --> 02:41:16.219
David S. Kong: it fall… it falls off, the fucking mechanical centipede keeps going. Are they really gonna stop? Because, like, one… one dude just, you know, tripped, you know?

1909
02:41:16.430 --> 02:41:21.119
Mike: I mean… What else are we gonna… we're probably not gonna learn anything else.

1910
02:41:24.840 --> 02:41:29.679
David S. Kong: This is weird. They're all on a giant, magical, moving, mechanical centipede. We have to, like.

1911
02:41:29.880 --> 02:41:36.420
David S. Kong: Knock it off of one. Socks. I like that one. Let's shoot it. Let's shoot, let's shoot it in the back. Let's shoot it in the butt.

1912
02:41:36.720 --> 02:41:37.390
Eric Rosenbaum: What the heck?

1913
02:41:37.390 --> 02:41:40.360
Mike: Iraq needs a briefing on the magical centipede.

1914
02:41:40.550 --> 02:41:43.879
Eric Rosenbaum: That was an amazing moment to come back, I gotta say.

1915
02:41:44.210 --> 02:41:44.910
Tim Sackton: Yeah.

1916
02:41:44.910 --> 02:41:47.730
Mike: So there's, like, 1,800 hobgoblins clinging to a.

1917
02:41:47.730 --> 02:41:51.490
Tim Sackton: 300 foot… No, 1800 times 2. 1,800 on each side.

1918
02:41:51.490 --> 02:42:01.660
Mike: There's, like… there's, like… 4,000 hobgoblins, well, 3,600 hopgoblins, clinging to, like, a 400-foot-long mechanical centipede that seems.

1919
02:42:01.660 --> 02:42:02.100
David S. Kong: Not the only.

1920
02:42:02.100 --> 02:42:08.069
Mike: Almost magical centipede that seems to be almost teleporting through the ash.

1921
02:42:08.900 --> 02:42:10.300
David S. Kong: It's like gliding over the ground.

1922
02:42:10.300 --> 02:42:10.960
Eric Rosenbaum: Yeah.

1923
02:42:10.960 --> 02:42:14.600
David S. Kong: And there's, like, some kind of leader dude with, like, melded armor or some shit.

1924
02:42:15.100 --> 02:42:23.419
David S. Kong: And we got close to it with the bat, but then it, like, one of the hobgoblins, like, ate the bat, and now we're trying to figure out how to get any more information.

1925
02:42:24.370 --> 02:42:28.409
David S. Kong: So, and we can't… we're trying to, like, oh, now our approach is, can we capture one of them?

1926
02:42:28.740 --> 02:42:47.160
David S. Kong: And so I was, like, we were talking about, oh, can we sweep in as an eagle and grab one? And I was like, oh, why don't we have Welby just, like, shoot one with an arrow, and then it just falls off the centipede? And are they really gonna… there's 4,000 hobgoblins, are they really gonna stop the centipede? Because, like, one hobgoblin fell off? And then we interrogate the one that we shot.

1927
02:42:47.290 --> 02:42:50.080
David S. Kong: Either we killed it and speak to dead, or we interrogate it.

1928
02:42:52.630 --> 02:42:55.390
David S. Kong: What do y'all? I think that's a pretty good… I think that's a pretty good plan.

1929
02:42:55.960 --> 02:42:57.509
Eric Rosenbaum: Yeah, dude, definitely.

1930
02:43:02.990 --> 02:43:04.310
Eric Rosenbaum: Chatasticity.

1931
02:43:04.420 --> 02:43:16.899
David S. Kong: I mean, the danger here is, of course, that they stop, and they're like, wait, where did that arrow come from? Let's stop what we're doing, and send all 4,000, like, you know, this is like, they're all on the same mission here, it's not like they can, like, branch off, you know? It's like….

1932
02:43:17.740 --> 02:43:18.080
Mike: Why?

1933
02:43:18.080 --> 02:43:18.950
Eric Rosenbaum: One way in the back.

1934
02:43:19.710 --> 02:43:24.169
Mike: We could… yes, way in the back, so I think what we do is we camp out, we're all invisible.

1935
02:43:24.360 --> 02:43:27.860
Mike: Except for Seeker 4, who has turned into a bug.

1936
02:43:28.030 --> 02:43:28.770
Mike: Right?

1937
02:43:29.060 --> 02:43:31.850
Mike: We camp out, and let them go past.

1938
02:43:32.220 --> 02:43:32.770
David S. Kong: Yes.

1939
02:43:32.770 --> 02:43:33.610
Eric Rosenbaum: A bug.

1940
02:43:33.850 --> 02:43:36.540
Mike: we animal-shaped to get here, right? So…

1941
02:43:36.920 --> 02:43:42.990
Mike: something little and hidden, right? Like, I don't know, a scorpion or some little creature that can hide under a rock, right?

1942
02:43:44.590 --> 02:43:48.229
Mike: We let it go past, Welby takes a shot, right?

1943
02:43:48.430 --> 02:43:52.210
Mike: But… If they stop, we just teleport.

1944
02:43:54.640 --> 02:43:56.570
Mike: Right? We could just run away.

1945
02:43:58.830 --> 02:44:00.909
Eric Rosenbaum: And the centipede is flying, or…?

1946
02:44:00.910 --> 02:44:01.999
Mike: No, it's like….

1947
02:44:02.150 --> 02:44:03.519
David S. Kong: It's like hovering over the ground.

1948
02:44:03.520 --> 02:44:08.039
Mike: Gliding over the ground like it's materializing legs, but they're not, like, quite touching the ground.

1949
02:44:08.040 --> 02:44:10.939
David S. Kong: It's like a sputer from Star Wars, but a giant centipede.

1950
02:44:12.630 --> 02:44:15.730
Eric Rosenbaum: And also carrying 3,600 hobgoblins.

